Dominion Energy Inc (D) said on Thursday it would keep fighting to get the Connecticut legislature to include power from the company's Millstone nuclear plant included in a state energy procurement plan. But NRG Energy Inc (NRG) vowed to fight Dominion's proposal, calling it "a cynical scheme that should not be rewarded."

















                                                    NRG shares up 9% as Wall Street cheers 'transformation' plan
                                                


                                                    MarketWatch – 
                                                    1:00 PM ET 07/13/2017
                                                


Stock gains more than 40% in its best ever week. Shares of NRG Energy Inc. (NRG) were on track for their best week on record following the energy company's plan to shift its strategy away from renewables and sell power plants and other assets worth up to $4 billion. NRG stock extended gains for a third session, up nearly 43% in that span.

















                                                    NRG Energy's stock rockets to biggest-ever one-day gain
                                                


                                                    MarketWatch – 
                                                    4:41 PM ET 07/12/2017
                                                


NRG Energy Inc.' s stock rocketed to its best-ever one-day percentage performance Wednesday, after the power plant operator revealed a "transformation plan" aimed cutting costs, slashing debt and selling assets. The stock closed up 29.39%, the biggest one-day gain since it came out of bankruptcy in late 2003. Volume ballooned to 47.4 million shares, about 11 times the full-day average. The previous biggest rally was 29.33% on Oct. 20, 2008. The stock closed at the highest level...

















                                                    NRG to sell assets, slash costs, bowing to activist pressure
                                                


                                                    MarketWatch – 
                                                    3:53 PM ET 07/12/2017
                                                


'Transformation plan' to involve selling up to $4 billion in assets. Buckling to pressure from activist investors, NRG Energy Inc. (NRG) said Wednesday that it would sell up to $4 billion in assets, slash costs and lower its debt as part of a "transformation plan." NRG, which owns and operates power plants, said it would sell $2.5 billion to $4 billion in assets, including possibly all of its interest in NRG Yield Inc., a dividend-generating company with renewable energy holdings.

















